      "raw_text": "HAS the railroad commission issue\nanything to do with this belief\"\n\n\nu believe 1t has,\" continued the\nbanker. who owns n few hundred\nmiles of interurban and street rail-\nways. Il can not see the good of a\nrailway commission. The railroads\nare business propositions conducted\non business principles by business\nmen. Rates are lowered when the\ncompanies can afford to. and neither\nn commission or anything else of tho\nkind can regulate such things. Traf-\nfic and trade conditions govern the\nchanges. Washington does not want\na railroad commission\"\n\n\nMr.. Furth is president OF the Puget\nSound National bank. the Puget\nSound Electric Railway company and\nthe Seattle Electric company."
